# ============================================================
#  SAFETY-FIRST .gitignore for a finance automation portfolio
#  Default stance: BLOCK anything that could carry real client
#  data, then explicitly allow only sanitized sample files.
# ============================================================

# --- Real data file types (blocked by default) ---
*.xlsx
*.xls
*.xlsm
*.csv
*.pdf
*.qbo
*.qbb
*.qbw

# --- Secrets / credentials ---
.env
.env.*
*.key
*.pem
*.pfx
credentials*
secrets*
*_token*
*apikey*
*api_key*

# --- Real client / engagement work-products (never publish) ---
#  Generic guards: block anything that looks like real engagement data.
#  (Add your own project-specific patterns locally; keep this file generic.)
**/client-data/
**/real-data/
**/private/
**/*_CONFIDENTIAL*
**/*review_package*/
**/*evidence_log*
**/*_pull_*.xlsx

# --- OS / tooling noise ---
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
node_modules/
.claude/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# ============================================================
#  ALLOWLIST: sanitized sample files you DELIBERATELY include.
#  Put dummy-data examples in a /samples folder and un-ignore
#  them explicitly here, e.g.:
# !samples/sample_reconciliation_DUMMY.csv
# ============================================================

# stray demo output dirs
out_demo/
**/out_demo/

# local helper scripts
/_*.js
